Canadian Dollar Advances as U.S. Stock-Index Futures Erase Their Decline

-- B y   D e n n i s   F i t z g e r a l d
-- 
2011-05-04T12:33:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-04/canadian-dollar-advances-as-u-s-stock-index-futures-erase-their-decline.html
The Canadian dollar advanced for the
first time in three days as U.S. stock-index futures erased
their drop, encouraging demand for assets related to global
economic growth.  The Canadian currency appreciated 0.2 percent to 95.12
cents versus the U.S. dollar at 8:32 a.m. in Toronto.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dennis Fitzgerald at 
 dfitzgerald5@bloomberg.net  